entry.tran: 没有污渍的；没有污点的；没有疤痕的；没有斑点的
entry.def: Something that is unmarked has no marks on it.

example.ex: Her shoes are still white and unmarked.
example.tran: 她的鞋仍然很白，没有任何污渍。

entry.tran: 没有标记的；没有标志的
entry.def: Something that is unmarked has no marking on it which identifies what it is or whose it is.

example.ex: He had seen them come out and get into the unmarked police car...
example.tran: 他看见他们走出来，上了一辆没有标志的警车。

example.ex: He lies in an unmarked grave at Elmton.
example.tran: 他长眠在爱尔莫顿一处无名冢下。

entry.tran: （球类比赛中）无人防守的，没被注意到的
entry.def: In a sport such as football, hockey, or basketball, if a player is unmarked, there are no players from the opposing team who are watching them in order to challenge them when they have control of the ball.

example.ex: Sheringham was unmarked as he met Anderton's free kick and headed in after nine minutes.
example.tran: 9分钟后，谢林汉姆在无人防守的情况下接安德顿开出的任意球头球破门得分。
